CONSULTING AUTOMOTIVE ENGINERS
CO. & D. R. BLACK AUG & 1920
AND TECHNICAL REPRESENTATIVES
THE AEROMARINE
NAVY-CRUISER
A large, perfectly appointed aerial
yacht for Week-end parties, off-shore
trips and long flights along the coast
THis Aeromarine aerial cruiser, which has
ample accommodations for ten passengers,
exclusive of pilot and pilot's mechanician, has
been designed for aerial voyages from New
York to Asbury Park, Atlantic City, Norfolk,
Washington, Baltimore, Southampton, New
Haven, New London, Newport, Miami and
other points on the Atlantic.
More luxurious in its appointments than even
the custom-built creations of the automobile world,
this new Aeromarine cruiser has a comfort all its
own. One gets the impression that one is seated
in a beautiful sedan, but instead of wheels, this
sedan has wings; instead of the jolting and bump-
ing to which one is subjected in even the finest
motor car, one experiences only the gentle sway-
ing of a cradle.
There is no sense of tenseness, no desire to
watch the road ahead of you, no nerve-racking
encounters at cross roads, no long ferry waits, no
straining up mountains or holding back on hills;
just a swift, smooth, pleasureable slipping through
the air in absolute comfort, to alight, betimes, at
your destination, thoroughly rested, refreshed by
